channel.title: Anyone know what I did wrong?
channel.description:
Well I was moving some shops around and editing some of them and after I compiled I tried to run the server and got this:
[code]PyroScape .. Online! Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: " " at java.lang.NumberFormatException.forInputString(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Unknown Source) at ShopHandler.loadShops(ShopHandler.java:117) at ShopHandler.<init>(ShopHandler.java:30) at server.main(server.java:35) [/code]
Any1 got an idea?

item.title: Anyone know what I did wrong?
item.dc:creator: @kihomura Kihomura
item.description:
@kihomura wrote:

You probably made a shop and like forgot to add an amount to the item, like

shop = 1	LMFAOshop				1	1	ITEMID	AMOUNT	ITEMID	AMOUNT	ITEMID	AMOUNT	ITEMID

Maybe

item.description:
@Scarr wrote:

Make sure you didn’t put spaces after the shop ID, e.g. Shop = ID(tab)1(tab)1(tab)etc…

and if you did do that, and know for sure you did, then after the ID of the shop, add another Tab.
